  "texts": [
    "Notably, so far, we do not know, if those changes in the average amount of tweets per user are simply driven by shifts in our active user sample (i.e., are those users that initially tweet a lot in RU leaving over time and this is why we see this decrease in the average?",
    "), or, if these changes are (at least partially) driven by behavioural changes in those users that remain active on Twitter (i.e., are the same users tweeting less in RU over time?).",
    "We address this through our tweet model described in Section \"Tweet Modelling\".",
    "We fit a generalized additive mixed model (GAMM) to predict the number of tweets made by each user in each language in each week, assuming a Poisson distribution.",
    "By incorporating both a smooth global time trend for each language, as well as user-specific random effects for each of the languages, we disentangle sample shifts (random effects) from behavioural changes (global trend)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}